		<description><![CDATA[I&#039;m only 16 min into watching this and I&#039;m blown away! What a great story of becoming a bass player from grade school up to age 29. Hey man, I&#039;m 57, just 2 years older, and can relate to all that you&#039;ve shared. I was at VaTech Elec Engg Grad school reading about MI when you went there in 1990! I remember those ads! Boy did I really desire to go, but my path was laid out. Anyway, now I&#039;m a beginner again, after 14 years, and finished going through your Module book 1. That&#039;s where I branched out from Root-Five to Root-Three! A milestone. Now inspired to continue practicing tonight for more walking bass lines. Will continue watching your podcast afterwards. Enjoyed watching your Motown video you recently posted on your weekly video site. 1-5-8 is the coolest. I appreciate you as a person and a teacher. Thanks Todd!]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;m only 16 min into watching this and I&#8217;m blown away! What a great story of becoming a bass player from grade school up to age 29. Hey man, I&#8217;m 57, just 2 years older, and can relate to all that you&#8217;ve shared. I was at VaTech Elec Engg Grad school reading about MI when you went there in 1990! I remember those ads! Boy did I really desire to go, but my path was laid out. Anyway, now I&#8217;m a beginner again, after 14 years, and finished going through your Module book 1. That&#8217;s where I branched out from Root-Five to Root-Three! A milestone. Now inspired to continue practicing tonight for more walking bass lines. Will continue watching your podcast afterwards. Enjoyed watching your Motown video you recently posted on your weekly video site. 1-5-8 is the coolest. I appreciate you as a person and a teacher. Thanks Todd!</p>
